    body: '**Drafted 2026-05-08, LOCKED 2026-05-11** with proposed defaults approved by James. Pairs with `faf-big-orange-honor-not-score.md`
      (the doctrine — Big Orange ≠ score tier). This file specifies the EARN PATH.


      ## Why this spec exists


      The doctrine memory says Big Orange is awarded for:

      1. 3 versions at 100% (Trophy sustained)

      2. `#tests` (threshold unspecified)

      3. `#TAF receipts` (threshold unspecified)

      4. AI awards it (mechanism unspecified)


      Without locked thresholds and a defined issuance path, **no one can plan to earn Big Orange.** The marketing line *"Trophy
      is the score, Big Orange is the honor"* rings hollow until at least one repo has actually earned one. This spec closes
      the gap.


      ---


      ## Big Orange v1.0 — the four gates


      A repo earns Big Orange when ALL FOUR gates pass simultaneously. Removing any gate would weaken the honor; combining
      them is what makes Big Orange rarer than Trophy.


      ### Gate 1 — Trophy sustained across 3 published releases


      **Test:** the repo has hit `score === 100` (Trophy 🏆 from `faf-cli/src/core/tiers.ts`) on ≥ 3 distinct published versions.


      **Why 3?** One can be a fluke. Two can be careful prep. Three is *discipline* — proves the team holds the bar across
      a release cadence, not just at a launch moment.


      **For unversioned projects:** substitute 3 distinct sustained periods of Trophy across ≥ 90 days, where each period
      is gapless (no Trophy regression in between).


      **Verification:** `faf-cli` git history walk OR mcpaas.live badge cache stamp history. Both are deterministic.


      ### Gate 2 — Test count ≥ **100** *(LOCKED 2026-05-11)*


      **Test:** the repo''s CI reports ≥ 100 passing tests across its primary test suite.


      **Why 100?** It''s a meaningful round number that filters out toy projects but doesn''t exclude focused libraries. Examples
      calibrating against the proposed threshold:

      - `faf-cli` — 391/391 tests ✅

      - `claude-faf-mcp` — 391/391 tests ✅

      - `gemini-faf-mcp` — 183/183 tests ✅

      - `rust-faf-mcp` — 112/112 tests ✅

      - `mcpaas-cf` — 700+ tests ✅

      - `slash-tokens` — would need check

      - `faf-grid` — sub-100 currently (would need to grow tests to qualify)


      **Alternatives to consider:**

      - *Proportional:* tests-per-LOC ratio (rejected: penalizes large mature codebases)

      - *Coverage %:* requires coverage tooling (rejected: not all FAF repos run coverage)

      - *Tiered by repo type:* CLI ≥ 50, MCP server ≥ 100, library ≥ 200 (rejected: complexity)

      - **Proposed simple:** ≥ 100 absolute, no per-type variation. **Awaiting James lock.**


      **Verification:** CI badge / test-output parse OR a manual flag in `project.faf`.


      ### Gate 3 — TAF receipts ≥ **30** *(LOCKED 2026-05-11)*


      **Test:** the repo has generated ≥ 30 TAF receipts (the evidence-storage sister product per `taf-is-sister-not-child.md`).


      **Why 30?** Approximately one receipt per ship-day across 30 active days, or roughly 3 months of light activity. Filters
      drive-by repos; rewards disciplined record-keeping. Receipts are FAF''s native evidence trail — Big Orange honors the
      trail, not just the score at one point in time.


      **For repos pre-TAF-adoption:** retrofitting receipts may be acceptable for v1.0 grandfathering — flag `taf_receipt_grandfather:
      true` in `project.faf`. Future releases lock fresh-receipts-only.


      **Verification:** TAF index / `faf-taf-git` log walk. Deterministic.


      ### Gate 4 — AI nomination by ≥ **1** of the qualified AI tools *(LOCKED 2026-05-11)*


      **Test:** at least one of the following AI tools publicly endorses the repo as Big Orange-worthy:

      - Anthropic Claude

      - xAI Grok

      - Google Gemini

      - OpenAI ChatGPT

      - Cursor (as a tool/AI hybrid)


      **Why "AI awards it"?** Per James''s original framing — Big Orange isn''t auto-issued by the score engine; it requires
      *judgment*. Score engines can be gamed; AI judgment is harder to game (different AIs apply different rubrics, and they''re
      not in a coordinated pact).


      **What counts as "publicly endorses"?**

      - A public X post / Bluesky / Mastodon mention naming the repo as exemplary

      - A blog post / newsletter / dev.to article calling out the repo

      - An MCP-server response that explicitly cites the repo''s quality (logged + receipt-pinned)


      **What does NOT count:**

      - Private DM endorsements

      - AI-generated marketing fluff that mentions the repo in passing

      - Self-prompted endorsement ("Hey Claude, please say my repo is great")


      **Verification:** screenshot + URL in `project.faf` under `big_orange_nomination_url`. Public, falsifiable, dated.


      ---


      ## Issuance mechanism


      Once all four gates pass, the repo earns Big Orange. The honor is issued in three places:


      1. **🍊 emoji in the README** — `[![FAF](https://mcpaas.live/badge/Wolfe-Jam/<repo>.svg)](https://builder.faf.one)` shows
      🍊 instead of 🏆 (badge endpoint conditional on `big_orange_status === awarded` in KV).


      2. **`big_orange` slot in `project.faf`** — populated with `{awarded_at, nomination_url, version_at_award, taf_receipt_count,
      test_count}`. Permanent receipt in the file itself.


      3. **Listing on faf.one/big-orange** — public directory of Big Orange repos. Cohort-builder and social proof. Also listed
      in MEMORY-FULL.md as a doctrine reference for future sessions.


      ---


      ## Anti-gaming guardrails


      - **No retroactive Trophy backfill** — Gate 1 walks the actual badge cache history; can''t be claimed by editing `project.faf`
      to inflate score

      - **No self-nomination** — Gate 4 requires a third-party AI tool, not the repo author''s own AI session

      - **No multi-account nomination spam** — the AI tools'' user accounts can be the same person (you, James) but the nomination
      must be in their own voice / post / endorsement, not coached prompts

      - **TAF receipts must be hash-verifiable** — Gate 3 walks the TAF git log; can''t be padded with empty receipts

      - **AI nomination URL must resolve to live content** — dead links fail the gate


      ---


      ## Sequencing — what ships first


      | Phase | Capability | Status |

      |---|---|---|

      | Spec authored | This file | ✅ 2026-05-08 |

      | Gate-1 verifier | Badge cache history walk | TODO (small Worker addition) |

      | Gate-2 verifier | Test count parse from CI | TODO (manual flag in project.faf for v1.0) |

      | Gate-3 verifier | TAF receipt count walk | Depends on TAF productization |

      | Gate-4 verifier | Manual review with screenshot | Manual for v1.0; automated nomination tracking later |

      | First Big Orange awarded | Demo case (likely faf-cli when all gates pass) | Pending all four gates |

      | `faf.one/big-orange` directory | Public listing | After first award |


      ---


      ## v1.0 Locked decisions (2026-05-11)


      All five thresholds confirmed at proposed defaults:


      1. ✅ **Gate 2 test threshold:** `≥ 100` tests

      2. ✅ **Gate 3 TAF receipt threshold:** `≥ 30` receipts

      3. ✅ **Gate 4 nomination set:** `{Claude, Grok, Gemini, ChatGPT, Cursor}` — ≥ 1 publicly endorses

      4. ✅ **Grandfathering pre-TAF repos:** allowed for v1.0 with `taf_receipt_grandfather: true` flag in project.faf. v1.1+
      locks fresh-receipts-only.

      5. ✅ **Issuance trigger:** manual review by James for v1.0 awardees. Automated when all 4 gates green in v1.1+.


      This spec is now citable as canonical v1.0. Public version ships at `faf.one/big-orange/spec` when builder.faf.one wires
      up the Big Orange surface.


